follow them, and eat it with them. (S. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 83.]) And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEawaA$iY","text_ar":"العَوَاشِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,) [when indeterminate,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaA$K","text_ar":"عَوَاشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates, (TA.) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are pasturing by night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) ―         -b2-  See also 1, former half. ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaA$iyapN","text_ar":"عَاشِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any man"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animal"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"looking and repairing, by night, towards the fire of a person who entertains guests."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n31213","headword_ar":"عَاشَ","root":"Ey$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, O, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEiy$u","text_ar":"يَعِيشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaA$N","text_ar":"مَعَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiy$N","text_ar":"مَعِيشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiy$apN","text_ar":"مَعِيشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiy$apN","text_ar":"عِيشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$uw$apN","text_ar":"عَيْشُوشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) and in the dial. of El-Azd"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuw$apN","text_ar":"مَعُوشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ew$","text_ar":"عوش"},{"kind":"text","text":", and TA.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lived;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * O, K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed life"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a particular manner of state:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became possessed of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say,."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaA$a fulaAnN","text_ar":"عَاشَ فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiy$apF raADiyapF","text_ar":"عِيشَةً رَاضِيَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one lived a pleasant"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life"},{"kind":"text","text":"(if we regard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiy$ap","text_ar":"عِيشَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a simple inf. n., as it is said to be above,) or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sort"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiy$apN","text_ar":"عِيشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","O","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B4/","headword_ar":"عاشر","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23402#ec29b5","body_html":"<span>العاشر: هو من نصبه الإمام على الطريق؛ ليأخذ الصدقات من التجار، مما يمرون به عليه عند اجتماع شرائط الوجوب.</span>"}]}}